   3.700565864488969*^9, 3.700565866479809*^9}, {3.7093869109392977`*^9, 
   3.7093869141048*^9}, {3.7136061689455657`*^9, 
   3.713606177290352*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"30b4974b-9a05-442f-bd5e-\
1e18a95455ac"],

Cell["\<\
Changed how peak reduction is handled by CombineData. You commented:

\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Set SnapPeaksToFrequencyGrid\[Dash]>True for the \
combination if any of the combined signals has \
SnapPeaksToFrequencyGrid\[Dash]>True; 
Set PeakReductionImplemented\[Rule]True only if all peak reductions are True\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]

By which I think you had the right idea in mind, but the syntax was changed \
from:

SnapPeaksToFrequencyGrid\[Rule]Or@@snappeaks,
PeakReductionImplemented\[Rule]And@@peakreds

to:

PeakReductionImplemented\[Rule]!And@@peakreds

to achieve the desired effect.


SnapPeaksToFrequencyGrid has been removed as it is now obsolete!\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.709386922996626*^9, 3.709386992335451*^9}, {
  3.713606186458056*^9, 3.713606190618826*^9}, {3.7136083373820543`*^9, 
  3.7136083393653436`*^9}, {3.7136085019171963`*^9, 3.7136085337088065`*^9}, {
  3.713608879867332*^9, 3.7136088884828615`*^9}, {3.713608929098154*^9, 
  3.713609030692763*^9}, {3.7136387392136116`*^9, 
  3.7136387519826794`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2baa4259-71e3-4224-922b-\
933530f6be12"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]]
},
